She walked to the door, just like in the old 
days, and opened it, and met 
a whoosh of winter air. She waited. 
The bones in the glass case rattled. Then 
the cat-shadow darted at her, through 
her legs, and slipped outside. It 
mingled with the shadows of insects. 
They will see again the shadows of 
bare branches, and leapt at the shadow 
of a bird. She looked at the tree, but 
there you are, surrounding it. Slant 
sun shines in. Bring it along, 
bone-reader, bring the banquet. F O 
R C N There was a crack in ecstasy; 
it split the oak with flameless fire 
